A group of guerrilla artists erected a 4-foot-high plaster bust of the NSA whistle-blower in Brooklyn's Fort Greene Park early Monday morning .
The artist, who has been living in exile in Russia since 2013, was spotted in the early hours Monday morning in the pre-dawn hours .
They hoisted the unsanctioned bust to the top of a Revolutionary War memorial and secured it with an adhesive material, adding his name to a column .